title: Officers try to save whale stranded in Queensland lagoon for weeks
text:
Officers try to save whale stranded i... Officers try to save whale stranded in Queensland lagoon for weeks Next Story Prev Story 3 hrs ago Read more: The Age 
Marine experts have hit the waters off Cairns in a bid to save a whale stranded in a reef lagoon for at least three weeks. Wildlife officers have gone to Elford reef in a bid to coax the whale, believed to be between six and eight metres long, to safety.   The Age.
